.TH "evm_inode_removexattr" 9 "evm_inode_removexattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
evm_inode_removexattr \- protect the EVM extended attribute
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" evm_inode_removexattr
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "const char *xattr_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
pointer to the affected dentry
.IP "xattr_name" 12
pointer to the affected extended attribute name
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Removing 'security.evm' requires CAP_SYS_ADMIN privileges and that
the current value is valid.
